In a #medium bowl{}, combine @coleslaw mix{4%oz}, @mayonnaise{2%tbsp}, half the @white wine vinegar{5%tsp}, @sugar{1/2%tsp}, @salt{}, and @pepper{} (all the vinegar and 1 tsp sugar for 4 servings).

Place @smoked pork burnt ends{10%oz}, @BBQ sauce{1/2%cup}, and @water{2%tbsp} (4 TBSP for 4 servings) in a #medium pan{}; cook over medium heat, breaking up pork into pieces, until pork is warmed through and sauce has thickened, ~{4-6%minutes}.

> Smoked Pork Burnt Ends are fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 160°.

Meanwhile, halve and toast @demi-baguette{2} in a #toaster{}.

Fill baguettes with BBQ pork and coleslaw. Divide sandwiches between plates and serve with @blue corn tortilla chips{1.5%oz} on the side.